<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-21T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-21T05:00:00-05:00" n="172" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6151/51: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-21T13:00:00+03:00">March
                                        21, 1941—1 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>561. The Moscow press this morning publishes a Tass announcement that
                                A. E. Bogomolov,<note n="18" xml:id="d172fn18">Alexander Efremovich
                                    Bogomolov.</note> the present Soviet Chargé d’Affaires in Vichy,
                                has been appointed Soviet Ambassador to France. The post has been
                                vacant since the recall last year of Surits<note n="19" xml:id="d172fn19">Yakov Zakharovich Surits (Suritz) had been
                                    declared <hi rend="italic">persona non grata</hi> in March
                                    1940.</note> at the request of the French Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>